    <h1 style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.6pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Assumption of Risk</h1>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'><strong>There is</strong> a significant risk of loss inherent in purchasing, trading, holding, and transacting Digital Assets. The following is a non-exhaustive list of risks involved in to purchase and hold Digital Assets:</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.6pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'><strong>You accept and Acknowledge:&nbsp;</strong></p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>There are risks associated with using crypto currency, including but not Limited to, the risk of hardware, software and internet connections, the risk of malicious Software introduction, and the risk that third parties may obtain unauthorized access to Information stored within your wallet. You accept and acknowledge that Social Mint will not be responsible for any communication failures, disruptions, errors, distortions or delays you may experience when using the Marketplace for transactions.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>The prices and liquidity of cryptocurrency assets (including any NFT&rsquo;s) are extremely volatile. Fluctuations in the price of other Digital Assets could materially and adversely affect the NFT&rsquo;s made available through the Marketplace, which may also be subject to significant price volatility. Social Mint cannot guarantee that any Creator(s) and or Collector(s) of NFT&rsquo;s will not lose money.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Our Marketplace do not store, send, or receive cryptocurrency assets on behalf of others. This is because Cryptocurrency assets exist only by virtue of the ownership record maintained on its supporting blockchain. Any transfer of cryptocurrency assets occurs within the supporting blockchain and not on the Marketplace. Transactions in NFT&rsquo;s may be irreversible, and, accordingly, losses due to fraudulent or accidental transactions may not be recoverable. Some transactions in NFT&rsquo;s shall be deemed to be made when recorded on a public ledger, which is not necessarily the date or time that you initiated the transaction.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Social Mint is not responsible for any issues with the blockchains, including forks, technical node issues or any other issues having fund losses as a result. You acknowledge that the cost and speed of transacting with cryptographic and blockchain-based systems such as Ethereum are variable and may increase at any time. &nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>By accessing and using the Marketplace, you represent that you understand the inherent Risks associated with using cryptographic and blockchain-based systems, and that you have a working knowledge of Digital Assets. Such systems may have vulnerabilities or other failures, or other abnormal behavior. &nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.15pt;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:.5pt;text-align:left;text-indent:0in;line-height:107%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;margin:0in;'>&nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Social Mint will not be liable to you for any losses you incur as the result of your use of the blockchain network. This includes, but is not limited to, losses, damages or claims arising from (i) Collector(s) error (e.g. Forgotten access information (such as passwords, private keys, seeds or mnemonics or incorrectly construed smart contracts or other transactions); (ii) server failure or data loss; (iii) corrupted wallet files; (iv) unauthorized access or activities by third parties, including but not limited to the use of viruses, phishing, or other means of attack against the Marketplace, the blockchain network, MetaMask and or Trust Wallet or any other Social Mint compatible browser or wallet. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>There are risks associated with purchasing Collector(s) generated content, including but not limited to, the risk of purchasing counterfeit assets, mislabeled assets, assets that are vulnerable to metadata decay, assets on smart contracts with bugs, and assets that may become untransferable. Social Mint reserves the right to hide collections, contracts, and assets affected</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>By any of these issues or by other issues. Assets you purchase may become inaccessible on Social Mint. Under no circumstances shall the inability to view or access your assets on Social Mint serve as grounds for a claim against Social Mint.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>You further acknowledge the risk that your Digital Assets may lose some or all of their value while they are supplied to or from the Marketplace. You further acknowledge that Social Mint is not responsible for any of these variables or risks and cannot be held liable for any resulting losses that you experience while accessing Marketplace. &nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>You agree and understand that you are solely responsible for determining the nature, potential value, suitability, and appropriateness of Digital Assets and these risks for yourself, and that Social Mint does not give advice or recommendations regarding Digital Assets, including the suitability and appropriateness of such assets. You agree and understand that your access and use of the Social Mint Marketplace is entirely at your own risk.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Use of the Marketplace, in particular for creating, buying or selling trading Digital Assets, may carry financial risk. Digital Assets are, by their nature, highly experimental, risky and volatile. You acknowledge and agree that you will access and use the Marketplace at your own risk. The risk of loss in trading Digital Assets can be substantial. You should, therefore, carefully consider whether such creating, buying or selling Digital Assets is suitable for you in light of your circumstances and financial resources. &nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>By purchasing, trading, holding, or transacting by way of the Social Mint Marketplace, you expressly assume all financial, economic, and technological risks associated with such transactions.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Furthermore, Creator(s) and or Collector(s) acknowledge and consent to the risk that the price of an NFT purchased on the Social Mint Marketplace may have been influenced by Creator(s) and or Collector(s) activity outside of the control of the Social Mint Marketplace. Social Mint Marketplace does not represent, guarantee, or warrant the accuracy or fairness of the price of any NFT sold or offered for sale on or off of the Marketplace. In addition, a lack of use or public interest in the creation and development of distributed Ecosystems could negatively impact the development of those ecosystems and related Marketplace applications, and could therefore also negatively impact the potential utility or value of a certain NFT.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>You accept all consequences of using the Marketplace, including the risk that you may lose access to your Digital Assets indefinitely. All transaction decisions are made solely by you. Notwithstanding anything in these terms, Social Mint accept no responsibility whatsoever for and will in no circumstances be liable to you in connection with use of the Marketplace for performing Digital Asset transactions. Under no circumstances will the operation of all or any portion of the Marketplace be deemed to create a relationship that includes the provision or tendering of investment advice.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>You are solely responsible for determining and paying what, if any, taxes are owed for your transactions for transactions both off and on the Marketplace. Neither Social Mint nor any Social Mint affiliates are responsible for determining or paying on your behalf the taxes for such transactions. &nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>The regulatory regime governing blockchain technologies, cryptocurrencies, and tokens is uncertain, and new regulations or policies may materially adversely affect the development of the Marketplace and the utility of NFT&rsquo;s.</p>
    <h1 style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.6pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Acceptable Use</h1>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>You are forbidden to use the Social Mint Marketplace, site, or your account to conduct electronic spamming or otherwise distribute any unsolicited or unauthorized advertising, promotional or marketing material, junk or chain messages</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>You are forbidden to use the Social Mint Marketplace, site, or your account to perform unlawful activities that violates any applicable laws (including but not limited to money laundering, terrorism financing and/or fraudulent activities) or immoral activities.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>You are forbidden to use the Social Mint Marketplace, site, or your account to engage in any activity which operates to defraud Social Mint, other Creator(s) and or Collector(s), or any other person, or to provide any false, inaccurate, or misleading information to Social Mint.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>You are forbidden to use the Social Mint Marketplace, site, or your account to upload content that is pornographic in nature , hurt religious sentiments , constitutes hate speech, is immoral or illegal, contains or is infected with viruses, malicious codes, trojan horses or any other harmful or deleterious program.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Modify or adapt the whole or any part of the Social Mint Marketplace and site or incorporate Social Mint into any other program or application.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>You are forbidden to use to disassemble, decompile, reverse-engineer or otherwise attempt to derive the source code, object code, underlying concepts, ideas and algorithms of Social Mint or any components thereof.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>You are forbidden to use the Social Mint Marketplace, site, or your account in any manner that would lead to infringement of our, our affiliates&rsquo; or any third party&rsquo;s intellectual property rights, including without limitation any copyright, patent or trademark. You undertake not to take or attempt to take any action or claim ownership of any property that infringes or would infringe upon our intellectual property interests.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>You are forbidden to use the Social Mint Marketplace, site, or your account in a way that could damage, disable, impair or compromise Social Mint or the provision of the Social Mint Marketplace or interfere with other Collector(s) or affect the reputation of Social Mint.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>You are forbidden to take any action to gain or attempt to gain unauthorized access to the account or wallets of other Creator(s) and or Collector(s).</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>You are forbidden to use take any action that imposes an unreasonable or disproportionately large burden or load on the Social Mint Marketplace infrastructure (including, but without limitation to our servers, networks, data centers and related or like equipment) and detrimentally interfere with, intercept or expropriate any system, data or information belonging to other Creator(s) and or Collector(s) of the Social Mint Marketplace.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>You are forbidden to engage in any other activities deemed inappropriate by us or which is in contravention of these terms or any applicable laws.</p>
    <h1 style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.6pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Marketplace</h1>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>The Social Mint Marketplace provides you with the opportunity to create (or as Social Mint call it, mint), sell, purchase, bid on, collect, trade, showcase and otherwise transact digital blockchain collectibles, which may be represented as a non-fungible token (&ldquo;NFT&rdquo;) linked with certain digital media and art (&ldquo;NFT Media&rdquo;). Social Mint facilitate transactions between Creator(s) and or Collector(s) of NFT. Social Mint collects revenue on the Social Mint Marketplace via transaction fees and other Marketplace applicable fees. NFT&rsquo;s transacted on the Social Mint Marketplace are considered &ldquo;Digital Assets&rdquo; as defined in the Social Mint terms. Social Mint reserves the right to be the final decision maker on any disputes arising from purchases via the Social Mint Marketplace, including in connection with any auctions or other purchase methods. &nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>You bear full responsibility for verifying the identity, legitimacy, and authenticity of assets you purchase through the Social Mint Marketplace. Notwithstanding indicators and messages that suggest verification, Social Mint makes no claims about the identity, legitimacy, or authenticity of assets on the Marketplace.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Each NFT is released automatically upon consummation of its sale through the relevant blockchain network if you elect to mint, buy, or sell any NFT&rsquo;s, any transactions that you engage in will be conducted solely through the relevant blockchain network governing such NFT. You will be required to make or receive payments exclusively through the cryptocurrency wallet you have connected to the Social Mint Marketplace. Social Mint will have no insight into or control over these payments or transactions, nor does Social Mint have the ability to reverse any transactions. &nbsp;</p>
    <h1 style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.6pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Terms of Sale</h1>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>By placing a bid or an order on or through Social Mint, you agree that you are submitting a binding offer to purchase such or service. Your order is accepted and confirmed once purchase is complete, and Social Mint displays the confirmation page (&quot;confirmation page&quot;). No refunds or returns are permitted except with respect to any statutory warranties or guaranties that cannot be excluded or limited by law.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Creator(s) may choose to provide certain rights to holders of their NFT(s), which may include, but is not limited to, physical items, special access, or other exclusive content (collectively, &ldquo;additional items&rdquo;). Any additional items will be provided directly to you from the Creator; Social Mint is not involved in such transactions and is not a party to such transactions. Notwithstanding the above, Social Mint may publish a description of the additional items on its Social Mint Marketplace on behalf of the Creator. If you own an NFT(s) that entitles you to additional items, you hereby consent to Social Mint sharing your contact information with the Creator to facilitate delivery of your additional items. <strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.6pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'><strong>Unless otherwise stated, transactions on the secondary market are only for NFT(s) and do not grant the Collector(s) the right to any additional items.&nbsp;</strong></p>
    <h1 style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.6pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Creator(s) and Collector(s)</h1>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>If you are using the Marketplace to purchase and trade NFT&rsquo;s, you are a &ldquo;<strong>Collector(s)</strong>,&rdquo; and if you are using the Marketplace to develop, create and or sell NFT&rsquo;s, you are a &ldquo;<strong>Creator(s)</strong>.&rdquo; If you are either a Collector(s) and or Creator(s), you agree to the following additional terms:</p>
    <h1 style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.6pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Purchase Terms<span style="font-weight:normal;">&nbsp;</span></h1>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Although the terms of sale for an NFT are displayed on the Social Mint Marketplace, all such terms are determined by the Collector(s) and or Creator(s) and the sale and purchase of NFT&rsquo;s are subject to such (e.g., with respect to the use of the NFT content, as defined below.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.15pt;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:.5pt;text-align:left;text-indent:0in;line-height:107%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;margin:0in;'>&nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Social Mint is not a party to any and all purchase terms, which are solely between the Collector(s) and Creator(s) and furthermore is not responsible for ensuring compliance with such terms or mediating or resolving any disputes with respect to such purchase terms, including, but not limited to, any disputes arising out of or related to the authenticity of the NFT or any intellectual property rights associated with such NFT. The Collector(s) and Creator(s) are entirely responsible for communicating, promulgating, agreeing to, and enforcing purchase terms, and for resolving any disputes arising from any breach of any purchase terms. Creator(s) and or Collector(s) must comply with and fulfill the purchase terms with respect to any NFT&rsquo;s that it sells. &nbsp;</p>
    <h1 style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.6pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Fees<span style="font-weight:normal;">&nbsp;</span></h1>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Creating, purchasing, trading, selling, transferring, and storing NFT&rsquo;s incur fees established at the sole discretion of Social Mint Marketplace.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Fees are paid via direct debit of the fee amount from the Collector(s)&rsquo;s account in the Social Mint Ecosystem. Fee amounts are set out in the relevant page on the Social Mint Marketplace site and include the NFT creation fee, the NFT additional copy fee, the NFT sale fee, the NFT transfer fee, NFT Trading fee and the fee for using blockchain space. The fee amounts may be changed by Social Mint at any time and at its discretion.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>If you are a Creator(s), you will receive revenue less the transaction fee for each initial sale of your NFT on the Social Mint Marketplace. The &ldquo;<strong>Transaction Fee</strong>&rdquo; means the percentage of the revenue generated from the initial sale of your NFT sale of an NFT that is listed on the listing interface, as agreed by you, when determining to list your NFT for sale. The transaction fee may be, but is not required to be, the sale percentage for all sales of NFT and may be changed from time to time prior to being agreed to on the listing interface with respect to.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>By transacting on the Social Mint Marketplace and by using the smart contracts, you hereby acknowledge, consent to, and accept all automated fees, commissions, and royalties for the sale of NFT on the Social Mint Marketplace. You hereby consent to and agree to be bound by the smart contracts&rsquo; execution and distribution of the fees, commissions, and royalties. You hereby waive any entitlement to royalties, commissions, or fees paid to another by operation of the smart contracts. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>You agree to pay Social Mint Marketplace a Commission on any transaction fees including supplementary fees for NFT transactions and authorize Social Mint to automatically charge you for any such fees and or commissions and deduct such fees (including the transaction fee) directly from your amounts paid by the Collector(s). You agree and understand that all fees, commissions, and royalties are transferred, processed, or initiated directly through one or more of the smart contracts on the blockchain network. &nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Furthermore, the blockchain network requires the payment of a transaction fee (a &ldquo;gas fee&rdquo;) for every transaction that occurs on the network, and thus every transaction occurring on Social Mint Marketplace. The &ldquo;<strong>Gas Fees</strong>&rdquo; mean the fees that fund the network of computers that run the decentralized blockchain network, meaning that you will need to pay a gas fee for each transaction that occurs via the blockchain network.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>The value of the gas fee changes, often unpredictably, and is entirely outside of the control of Social Mint Marketplace. You acknowledge that under no circumstances will a contract, agreement, offer, sale, bid, or other transaction on Social Mint Marketplace be invalidated, revocable, retractable, or otherwise unenforceable on the basis that the gas fee for the given transaction was unknown, too high, or otherwise unacceptable to you. You also acknowledge and agree that gas is non-refundable under all circumstances.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>You further agree to the payments made to Creator(s) do not include any taxes (as defined below), and Social Mint shall have no responsibility for payment of such taxes regardless of the taxing authority. Each party shall be responsible for all taxes imposed on its income or property. As used herein, &ldquo;<strong>Taxes</strong>&rdquo; means the taxes, duties, levies, tariffs, and other governmental charges that you may be required by law to collect and remit to governmental agencies, and other similar municipal, state, federal and national indirect or other withholding and personal or corporate income taxes.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Social Mint reserve the right to report any activity occurring using the Marketplace to relevant tax authorities as required under Marketplace applicable law.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>All transactions related to NFT&rsquo;s are final. All fees paid and/or withheld are nonrefundable, except for in certain cases at the sole discretion of Social Mint Marketplace.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>If a Collector(s) does not have the funds to pay a fee, the Collector(s)&rsquo;s account may be blocked until the Funds are paid to the Marketplace.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.6pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'><strong>Fees paid to Social Mint are as follows:&nbsp;</strong></p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>In addition to the gas fee, each time you utilize a smart contract to conduct a purchase transaction with another Collector(s) via the Marketplace, you authorize us to collect:</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>A commission of 5% of the total value of that transaction; and</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>A further 2.5% commission for all proceeding secondary sales on the Social Mint Marketplace.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>You acknowledge and agree that the commission will be transferred directly to us through the blockchain network as part of your payment.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.15pt;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:.5pt;text-align:left;text-indent:0in;line-height:107%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;margin:0in;'>&nbsp;</p>
    <h1 style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.6pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Creator(s) Rights</h1>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>By posting or submitting your content to the Social Mint Marketplace, you represent and warrant that you have, or have obtained, all rights, licenses, consents, permissions, and/or authority necessary to grant the rights granted herein for your content. You agree that your content will not contain material subject to copyright or other proprietary rights, unless you have the necessary permission or are otherwise legally entitled to post the material and to grant us the license described above. &nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>As the copyright owner, the Creator has the right to reproduce, prepare derivatives of, distribute, and display or perform the art content and collection content. &nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>The Creator hereby acknowledges, understands, and agrees that selling such Digital Asset(s)on the Marketplace constitutes an express representation, warranty, and covenant that the Creator (a) has not sold, tokenized or created another cryptographic token, and (b) will not, and will not cause another to, sell, tokenize, or create another cryptographic token, in each case representing a digital collectible for the same art content underlying such Digital Asset(s).</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>As a Creator(s), you understand and agree that:</p>
    <ul style="list-style-type: undefined;margin-left:0in;">
        <li>You are responsible for the accuracy and content of your creations;</li>
        <li>Any &nbsp;creation that violates any of Social Mint&rsquo;s policies may be obfuscated or deleted by Social Mint, in its sole discretion;</li>
        <li>You will not use the Digital Asset incorporated into your creations for the creation of additional non-fungible tokens;</li>
        <li>You will respect the intellectual property of others; and</li>
        <li>You will not coordinate pricing with other Creator(s).</li>
    </ul>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Social Mint reserve the right, in our sole discretion, to prohibit you from uploading your creations. Although Social Mint is not required to monitor any Collector(s) content, Social Mint may, in our sole discretion, remove Collector(s) content at any time and for any reason without notice. Social Mint may monitor Collector(s) content to detect and prevent fraudulent activity or violation of these terms of use.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Social Mint does not provide any guarantees or assurances of the uniqueness, originality, or quality of metadata. In the absence of an explicit legal agreement between Social Mint, the Creator of a work of art and the buyer of an NFT, there can be no guarantees or assurances that the purchase or ownership of the NFT gives any kind of property license or right to the work of art itself or intellectual property connected to it, despite the fact that the Collector(s) may rightfully own the NFT connected to the work of art.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.15pt;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:.5pt;text-align:left;text-indent:0in;line-height:107%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;margin:0in;'>&nbsp;</p>
    <h1 style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.6pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Collector(s) Rights</h1>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>When you purchase an NFT through the Marketplace, you own all personal property rights to the electronic record that comprises the NFT. Unless expressly specified in the purchase terms,</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Such rights do not include the ownership of the intellectual property rights in any NFT Content. &nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>The Collector(s) receives a cryptographic token representing the Creator&rsquo;s art content as a piece of property, but does not own the art content itself or any intellectual property rights therein. &nbsp;The Collector(s) may display and share the art content, but the Collector(s) does not have any legal ownership, right, or title to any copyrights, trademarks, or other intellectual property rights to the art content, except the limited license to the art content granted by these terms. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Upon legally collecting and obtaining ownership of any Digital Asset(s)launched on the Marketplace, the Collector(s) receives from the Creator(s) of such Digital Asset(s)a limited, worldwide, non-assignable and non-transferable (except as expressly set forth below), nonsublicensable, royalty-free license to display the art content underlying such Digital Asset(s)solely for the Collector(s)&rsquo;s non-commercial purposes, including the right to display such art content privately or publicly: (i) for the purpose of promoting or sharing the Collector(s)&rsquo;s purchase of, ownership of, or interest in such Digital Asset(s) (ii) for the purpose of sharing, promoting, discussing, or commenting on such art content; (iii) on third party Marketplaces, exchanges, or Marketplaces in association with an offer to sell, or trade, the Digital Asset(s); and (iv) within decentralized virtual environments, virtual worlds, virtual galleries, virtual museums, or other navigable and perceivable virtual environments (the &ldquo;Collector(s) license&rdquo;). &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Upon any sale or transfer of the Digital Asset(s) to another Collector(s), (a) the foregoing license will automatically transfer to such other Collector(s), and such other Collector(s) will be deemed the &ldquo;Collector(s)&rdquo; (for purposes of such Digital Asset(s)and the Collector(s) license to the underlying art content) and will be subject to these terms and (b) the Creator and or seller(s) or transferor of such Digital Asset(s)will cease to have any further rights to such art content. &nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>While the Collector(s) has the right to sell, trade, transfer, or use their Digital Asset(s) the Collector(s) may not make commercial use of the Digital Asset(s)or its underlying art content.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>NFT&rsquo;s may be subject to terms directly Social Mint Collector(s)(s) and Creator(s) with respect to the use of the NFT content. The Collector(s), Creator(s) are entirely responsible for communicating, agreeing to, and enforcing purchase terms. &nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>All fees related to the purchase of NFT&rsquo;s are non-refundable except at the sole discretion of the Social Mint (for service fees and other fees within its control).</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Social Mint will have no insight into or control over the transfers of the Digital Assets by you to us, nor do Social Mint have the ability to reverse any transactions. With that in mind, Social Mint will have no liability to you or to any third party for any claims or damages that may arise as a result of any transactions that you engage in order to purchase.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Collector(s) understands and agrees that Social Mint will not accept or take custody over any NFT&rsquo;s belonging to the Collector(s) of any funds or Digital Assets of the Collector(s) and has no responsibility or control over the foregoing. &nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Collector(s) is solely responsible to indicate correct electronic wallet address to which the NFT&rsquo;s should be transferred. You should make sure that the address you provide us is correct and that your electronic wallet is able to receive (support) the NFT&rsquo;s. Some electronic wallets may not support the NFT&rsquo;s in which case you may lose the tokens, for which Social Mint will bear no liability and you will not be granted with additional NFT&rsquo;s. The Social Mint is not responsible for any delays, losses, costs, non-delivery of NFT&rsquo;s, or other issues arising from the failure to provide, or providing an inaccurate or incomplete electronic wallet address.</p>
    <h1 style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.6pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Rules for Buying an NFT</h1>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>The Collector(s) has the option of buying an NFT either via auction or at a fixed price, and payment takes place in various cryptocurrencies. To purchase an NFT, the Collector(s) must have an account in the Social Mint Marketplace ecosystem.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>If the Collector(s) acquires an NFT at auction, they must place a bid to participate in the auction. The highest bid placed will buy the NFT for sale. The bid amount is the minimum amount needed to raise the last bid and place a new one. If the Collector(s)&rsquo;s account does not have any or has insufficient cryptocurrency, the Collector(s) will receive due notice of this. Once placed, a bid cannot be canceled, and the Collector(s)&rsquo;s funds will be blocked until another Collector(s) raises the bid or the auction is finished. The Collector(s) who places the highest bid will acquire the NFT for sale, the smart contract is executed, and the required amount is withdrawn from their account balance to pay for the NFT.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>If an NFT is purchased at a fixed price, the Collector(s) acquires the NFT for sale at the full listed price, the smart contract is executed, and the required amount is withdrawn from their account balance to pay for the NFT, along with the Marketplace fee set out in the relevant page on Social Mint.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Payments are made via direct debit from the Collector(s)&rsquo;s account in the Social Mint ecosystem.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Social Mint Marketplace bears no obligations before the Collector(s) to store or help restore any NFT-media connected to a Collector(s)&rsquo;s NFT.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.15pt;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:.5pt;text-align:left;text-indent:0in;line-height:107%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;margin:0in;'>&nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>The Collector(s) bears full liability for checking the authenticity, legality, and identity of any NFT they purchase. Social Mint Marketplace does not give any guarantees or assurances regarding the identity, legality, or authenticity of any NFT sold. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Social Mint Marketplace reserves the right to make final decisions on any disputes arising in connection with purchases.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:9.0pt;margin-left:0in;text-align:left;text-indent:0in;line-height:107%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'><a href="https://www.lawinsider.com/clause/restrictions"><strong><span style="color:black;">Restrictions</span></strong></a><a href="https://www.lawinsider.com/clause/restrictions"><span style="color:black;text-decoration:none;">&nbsp;</span></a></p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>You agree that you may not, nor permit any third party to do or attempt to do any of the foregoing without Creator&rsquo;s express prior written consent in each case:</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Modify the art for your purchased NFT in any way, including, without limitation, the shapes, designs, drawings, attributes, or color schemes (your use of extensions will not constitute a prohibited modification hereunder);</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Use the art for your purchased NFT&rsquo;s to advertise, market, or sell any third party product or service;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Use the art for your purchased NFT&rsquo;s in connection with images, videos, or other forms of media that depict hatred, intolerance, violence, cruelty, or anything else that could reasonably be found to constitute hate speech or otherwise infringe upon the rights of others;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Use the art for your purchased NFT&rsquo;s in movies, videos, or any other forms of media, unless it is solely for your own personal, non-commercial use;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Sell, distribute for commercial gain (including, without limitation, giving away in the hopes of eventual commercial gain), or otherwise commercialize merchandise that includes, contains, or consists of the art for your purchased NFT&rsquo;s;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Attempt to trademark, copyright, or otherwise acquire additional intellectual property rights in or to the art for your purchased NFT&rsquo;s; or,</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Otherwise utilize the art for your purchased NFT&rsquo;s for your or any third party&rsquo;s commercial benefit.</p>
    <h1 style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.6pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Verification and payment</h1>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>When you make purchases through the Social Mint Marketplace, including, without limitation, any purchase for NFT&rsquo;s, you must provide and maintain valid payment information in connection with your Social Mint account (as defined in the Social Mint terms) with us. You represent and warrant that you are authorized to use the payment method you use via the Social Mint Marketplace to make any purchase. You authorize us to charge your payment method for the total amount of your purchase price. Your order may be suspended or cancelled for any reason, including if the payment method cannot be verified, is invalid or is otherwise not acceptable. Other payments terms for purchases are set forth in the relevant sections of the Social Mint terms. Social Mint have no liability to you or to any third party for any claims or damages that may arise as a result of any payments or transactions that you engage in via the Social Mint Marketplace, or any other payment or transactions that you conduct via the Social Mint Marketplace. Social Mint do not provide refunds for any purchases that you might make on or through the Social Mint Marketplace &ndash; whether for NFT&rsquo;s or anything else. You will be solely responsible to pay any and all sales, use, value-added and other taxes, duties, and assessments (except taxes on our net income) now or hereafter claimed or imposed by any governmental authority associated with your use of the Social Mint Marketplace or NFT&rsquo;s, except for income taxes levied on us as a result of such purchases of NFT&rsquo;s.</p>
    <h1 style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.6pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Rules for Selling an NFT</h1>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>By selling an NFT via Social Mint Marketplace, the Collector(s) affirms and guarantees that they possess all legal intellectual property rights to the NFT, and the Collector(s) has legal permission from the owner of the intellectual property to sell the NFT.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>The Collector(s) has the option of selling NFT either via auction or at a fixed price, and payment takes place in various cryptocurrencies supported by the Social Mint ecosystem.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>The choice of whether to sell by auction or at a fixed price is made by the Collector(s) when the token is created. The Collector(s) also determines the initial price and bidding duration. &nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:-.65pt;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:left;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Proceeds from the sale of the NFT less any and all fees will go to the Collector(s)&rsquo;s account in the Social Mint ecosystem as soon as the smart contract for the NFT sale is executed. As soon as the smart contract for the NFT sale is executed, a fee is withheld from the Collector(s).</p>
    <h1 style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.6pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Minted Marketplace Program</h1>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>As part of the Social Mint Marketplace, Social Mint offers a Premium Marketplace (the &ldquo;Minted Marketplace&rdquo;) which allows Artists(s) that are invited by Social Mint to create Works on the behalf of Collector(s). &nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>The Invited Artist(s) can enter into an agreement with any invited Collector(s) that outlines the terms of use of the Social Mint Marketplace for the invited Artist(s). &nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>The invited Artist(s) hereby presents the Social Mint Marketplace with the perpetual, irrevocable and exclusive right and license to use, reproduce, and display the Artist(s) works in connection with the promotion of the works and NFT&rsquo;s related to them, and the Social Mint Marketplace itself.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>At the request of the Social Mint Marketplace, the invited Artist(s) will cooperate with Social Mint Marketplace to verify the authenticity of the Artist(s)&rsquo;s works of art and NFT&rsquo;s. The invited Artist(s) recognizes and agrees that Social Mint Marketplace will collect a commission as established in a separate agreement Social Mint the parties.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>At the request of Social Mint, an invited Artist(s) will support the Social Mint Marketplace in the promotion or marketing of the NFT Artist(s) by participating in marketing events Marketplace approved by both parties. In connection with the promotion of NFT, an invited Artist(s) shall grant the Social Mint Marketplace the right to use the name, image, photograph, creative portrait, biography, signature, and if it is a legal entity, the brand name, logo, and other business attributes of the invited Artist(s) exclusively in connection with marketing and promoting the NFT Artist(s).</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>The invited Artist(s) will not promote or sell NFT&rsquo;s in a way that gives Collector(s) the impression that the NFT&rsquo;s are investment products or that they can count on capital gains or receiving profits from purchasing the NFT&rsquo;s or indicate that the NFT&rsquo;s can be characterized as securities or any other form of regulated investment product in any jurisdiction.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:12.55pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>The Minted Marketplace is for the following:</p>
    <ol style="list-style-type: undefined;margin-left:6.100000000000001px;">
        <li>The Artist is in the business of creating and supplying artwork; &nbsp;</li>
        <li>The Minter wishes to commission the Artist to create and supply such artwork for the Minter</li>
        <li>The Artist understands and acknowledges that the such artwork will be used by the Minter for the purposes of creating and selling a Digitized Token - NFT. &nbsp;</li>
    </ol>
    <h1 style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.4pt;margin-left:-.25pt;text-indent:-.5pt;line-height:111%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black;'>Artist&apos;s obligations<span style="font-weight:normal;">&nbsp;</span></h1>
